---
import Base from "../../layouts/Base.astro";
import { productAtlas, productAtlasCategories } from "../../lib/product-atlas";

const title = "AI product atlas — Armalo";
const description =
  "A public-safe atlas of 120 buildable AI products for businesses, SMBs, teams, creators, and individuals, fulfilled through Hermes.";
const groups = productAtlasCategories.map((category) => ({
  category,
  products: productAtlas.filter((product) => product.category === category),
}));
const topMoneyMakers = productAtlas.slice(0, 20);
---

<Base title={title} description={description}>
  <article class="mx-auto max-w-5xl px-6 pt-16 pb-24">
    <a href="/#atlas" class="text-sm text-accent link-quiet hover:text-ink">
      ← Back to the catalogue
    </a>
    <header class="mt-10 max-w-3xl">
      <p class="text-2xs uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-accent">
        Product atlas · 120 buildable offers · ranked 2026-07-17
      </p>
      <h1 class="mt-3 text-4xl text-ink">
        The AI product surface is bigger than one app.
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-6 text-lg leading-relaxed text-ink-soft">
        Buyers are not shopping for “AI” in the abstract. They are buying a
        faster response, a cleaner close, fewer unpaid invoices, better
        documentation, more useful marketing, and time back. This atlas turns
        those jobs into recognizable offers that can be piloted, packaged, and
        fulfilled.
      </p>
      <div
        class="mt-8 border-y border-line py-5 text-sm leading-relaxed text-ink-soft"
      >
        <p>
          Hermes Agent is the fulfillment brain behind the catalogue: it turns
          the sold brief into tuning, integrations, approvals, testing, launch,
          and support. The public status boundary still matters. An atlas entry
          is a buildable category hypothesis, not evidence of a live
          destination, customer, revenue, or business outcome.
        </p>
      </div>
    </header>

    <section class="mt-14" aria-labelledby="how-to-buy-heading">
      <p class="text-2xs uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-accent">How to buy</p>
      <h2 id="how-to-buy-heading" class="mt-2 text-2xl text-ink">
        Start with a job. End with a measured handoff.
      </h2>
      <div
        class="mt-6 grid gap-6 text-sm leading-relaxed text-ink-soft md:grid-cols-4"
      >
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-base text-ink">1. Diagnose</h3><p class="mt-2">
            Choose the workflow, owner, system of record, and costly failure
            mode.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-base text-ink">2. Pilot</h3><p class="mt-2">
            Bound the data, authority, and success metric before broadening
            scope.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-base text-ink">3. Fulfill</h3><p class="mt-2">
            Hermes tunes the agent, wires the integrations, and keeps human
            approvals visible.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-base text-ink">4. Prove</h3><p class="mt-2">
            Advance from planned to live only with runtime and business
            evidence.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-16" aria-labelledby="ranking-heading">
      <p class="text-2xs uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-accent">
        Money-maker order
      </p>
      <h2 id="ranking-heading" class="mt-2 text-2xl text-ink">
        Sell these first. Fulfill them repeatedly.
      </h2>
      <p class="mt-4 max-w-3xl text-sm leading-relaxed text-ink-soft">
        The order is a prioritization instrument, not a revenue claim. Each
        offer is scored out of 100: buyer money potential ×4, repeatable scale
        ×3, and Hermes fulfillment fit ×3. Each dimension is scored from 1–10. A
        score rewards a painful, budgeted workflow that can be packaged across
        customers and operated with bounded tools, context, and human approvals.
      </p>
      <ol class="mt-8 divide-y divide-line border-y border-line">
        {
          topMoneyMakers.map((product) => (
            <li class="grid gap-4 py-5 md:grid-cols-[2rem_1.4fr_1fr] md:gap-8">
              <span class="text-sm font-medium tabular-nums text-accent">
                {String(product.rank).padStart(2, "0")}
              </span>
              <div>
                <h3 class="text-lg text-ink">{product.name}</h3>
                <p class="mt-1 text-xs uppercase tracking-wide text-ink-faint">
                  {product.category}
                </p>
                <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-relaxed text-ink-soft">
                  {product.job}
                </p>
              </div>
              <div>
                <p class="text-sm text-ink">
                  Priority <strong>{product.priorityScore}/100</strong>
                </p>
                <p class="mt-1 text-xs leading-relaxed text-ink-soft">
                  Money {product.moneyScore}/10 · Scale {product.scaleScore}/10
                  · Hermes {product.hermesScore}/10
                </p>
                <p class="mt-2 text-xs leading-relaxed text-ink-faint">
                  {product.revenueModel}
                </p>
              </div>
            </li>
          ))
        }
      </ol>
    </section>

    <nav
      aria-label="Atlas categories"
      class="mt-14 flex flex-wrap gap-x-4 gap-y-2 border-y border-line py-4 text-sm text-ink-soft"
    >
      {
        groups.map((group) => (
          <a
            class="link-quiet hover:text-ink"
            href={`#${group.category.toLowerCase().replaceAll(" ", "-")}`}
          >
            {group.category}
          </a>
        ))
      }
    </nav>

    <div class="mt-12 space-y-14">
      {
        groups.map((group) => {
          const id = group.category.toLowerCase().replaceAll(" ", "-");
          return (
            <section id={id} aria-labelledby={`${id}-heading`}>
              <div class="flex items-baseline justify-between gap-4 border-b border-line pb-3">
                <h2 id={`${id}-heading`} class="text-2xl text-ink">
                  {group.category}
                </h2>
                <span class="text-xs text-ink-faint">
                  {group.products.length} offers
                </span>
              </div>
              <ul class="mt-5 grid gap-5 md:grid-cols-2">
                {group.products.map((product) => (
                  <li id={product.slug} class="border-t border-line pt-4">
                    <details open={product.rank <= 20}>
                      <summary class="cursor-pointer list-none">
                        <div class="flex items-start justify-between gap-3">
                          <h3 class="text-lg text-ink">{product.name}</h3>
                          <span class="text-2xs font-medium tabular-nums text-accent">
                            #{String(product.rank).padStart(2, "0")} ·{" "}
                            {product.priorityScore}/100
                          </span>
                        </div>
                        <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-relaxed text-ink-soft">
                          <strong class="font-medium text-ink">Job:</strong>{" "}
                          {product.job}
                        </p>
                      </summary>
                      <div class="mt-4 space-y-5 border-l border-line pl-4">
                        <div>
                          <p class="text-2xs uppercase tracking-wide text-accent">
                            Feature blueprint
                          </p>
                          <ul class="mt-2 space-y-1 text-sm leading-relaxed text-ink-soft">
                            {product.features.map((feature) => (
                              <li>— {feature}</li>
                            ))}
                          </ul>
                        </div>
                        <div>
                          <p class="text-2xs uppercase tracking-wide text-accent">
                            ICP and buying trigger
                          </p>
                          <dl class="mt-2 space-y-2 text-sm leading-relaxed text-ink-soft">
                            <div>
                              <dt class="font-medium text-ink">Company</dt>
                              <dd>{product.icp.company}</dd>
                            </div>
                            <div>
                              <dt class="font-medium text-ink">Buyer</dt>
                              <dd>{product.icp.buyer}</dd>
                            </div>
                            <div>
                              <dt class="font-medium text-ink">Trigger</dt>
                              <dd>{product.icp.trigger}</dd>
                            </div>
                            <div>
                              <dt class="font-medium text-ink">Disqualifier</dt>
                              <dd>{product.icp.disqualifier}</dd>
                            </div>
                          </dl>
                        </div>
                        <div>
                          <p class="text-2xs uppercase tracking-wide text-accent">
                            Marketing and expansion
                          </p>
                          <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-relaxed text-ink-soft">
                            {product.marketing.positioning}
                          </p>
                          <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-relaxed text-ink-soft">
                            <strong class="font-medium text-ink">
                              Channels:
                            </strong>{" "}
                            {product.marketing.channels.join(" · ")}
                          </p>
                          <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-relaxed text-ink-soft">
                            <strong class="font-medium text-ink">
                              Proof asset:
                            </strong>{" "}
                            {product.marketing.proofAsset}
                          </p>
                          <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-relaxed text-ink-soft">
                            <strong class="font-medium text-ink">
                              Expansion:
                            </strong>{" "}
                            {product.marketing.expansion}
                          </p>
                        </div>
                        <p class="text-2xs uppercase tracking-wide text-ink-faint">
                          Planned · unavailable · not yet proven · Hermes
                          fulfillment candidate
                        </p>
                      </div>
                    </details>
                  </li>
                ))}
              </ul>
            </section>
          );
        })
      }
    </div>

    <section
      class="mt-16 border-t border-line pt-8"
      aria-labelledby="sources-heading"
    >
      <p class="text-2xs uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-accent">
        Demand signals
      </p>
      <h2 id="sources-heading" class="mt-2 text-2xl text-ink">
        Why these categories are here
      </h2>
      <p class="mt-4 max-w-3xl text-sm leading-relaxed text-ink-soft">
        The atlas follows current buying signals: customer service and marketing
        are among the leading business GenAI functions; small firms are adopting
        content, marketing, and service tools; and enterprise leaders are
        planning agent integration across functions. Current commercial
        packaging also shows the shape of the market: outcome or conversation
        pricing for service agents, consumption credits for enterprise agents,
        and recurring enterprise knowledge subscriptions. These sources
        establish category demand, not Armalo customer proof.
      </p>
      <ul class="mt-5 space-y-2 text-sm">
        <li>
          <a
            class="link-quiet text-accent hover:text-ink"
            href="https://www.gartner.com/en/insights/generative-ai-for-business"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer">Gartner · business GenAI functions ↗</a
          >
        </li>
        <li>
          <a
            class="link-quiet text-accent hover:text-ink"
            href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/worklab/work-trend-index/2025-the-year-of-the-frontier-firm-is-born"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            >Microsoft Work Trend Index · agentic enterprise planning ↗</a
          >
        </li>
        <li>
          <a
            class="link-quiet text-accent hover:text-ink"
            href="https://www.uschamber.com/technology/empowering-small-business-the-impact-of-technology-on-u-s-small-business"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            >U.S. Chamber · small-business AI adoption ↗</a
          >
        </li>
        <li>
          <a
            class="link-quiet text-accent hover:text-ink"
            href="https://sbecouncil.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/SBE-Small-Business-Technology-Survey-March-2025-Ver-2.0-1.pdf"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            >SBE Council · popular small-business AI applications ↗</a
          >
        </li>
        <li>
          <a
            class="link-quiet text-accent hover:text-ink"
            href="https://www.salesforce.com/agentforce/pricing/"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            >Salesforce Agentforce · consumption and conversation pricing ↗</a
          >
        </li>
        <li>
          <a
            class="link-quiet text-accent hover:text-ink"
            href="https://www.intercom.com/learning-center/ai-customer-service-agent-pricing-comparison"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            >Intercom · customer-agent pricing comparison ↗</a
          >
        </li>
        <li>
          <a
            class="link-quiet text-accent hover:text-ink"
            href="https://www.glean.com/press/glean-surpasses-200m-in-arr-for-enterprise-ai-doubling-revenue-in-nine-months"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer">Glean · enterprise AI ARR signal ↗</a
          >
        </li>
        <li>
          <a
            class="link-quiet text-accent hover:text-ink"
            href="https://www.ipsos.com/en-ca/canadian-small-business-owners-embracing-ai-wide-variety-functions"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            >Ipsos / TD · small-business buying use cases ↗</a
          >
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>
  </article>
</Base>
